irregularity or moral impropriety by MPs and some had referred to Mr Mates
in this context.
'Mr Mates takes the greatest exception to such inferences since at the time
of his resignation both the prime minister and the attorney-general
specifically stated that he had acted with complete propriety,' Denton Hall
said.
